{"key":"post-9501774","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9501774</id>\n<content>DON'T use the salt method for growing mushrooms, as said repeatedly above.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A mechanical hygrometer has a human hair attached to a spring, which is attached to the dial.&amp;nbsp; As the humidity changes, the human hair stretches and compacts, which shows the humidity.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Such a method is only accurate through a narrow humidity range.&amp;nbsp; If you want it to be accurate to read ambient humidity in your house, use the salt method.&amp;nbsp; If you want it to be accurate in your fruiting chamber, use the damp towel method.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9501782</next>\n<prev>9501041</prev>\n<first>9496362</first>\n<last>9501784</last>\n<when>1230402644</when>\n<utime>12/27/08 08:30 PM</utime>\n</post>"}